answers.answer: Protein alone will not cause you to have an early delivery, however protein in your urine can be a sign of a more serious problem like preeclampsia or renal problems. If those problems become a risk to your health it's a not uncommon for the drs to want to take baby early.
Is it normal though? Or rare

Protein in your urine can be normal, if you've consumed a lot of protein you will likely spill some into your urine. However, like I said it can be a sign of other problems too. If your Dr is concerned they will usually order other tests and monitor your BP. Problems like preeclampsia are not exceedingly uncommon, but they don't happen to everyone. Preeclampsia needs to be closely watched because if not controlled it can easily develop into eclampsia which can often be fatal.
